And when the days of her purification according to the law
of Moses were accomplished, they brought him to Jerusalem, to present
\add him\add* to the Lord;

And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold,
this \add child\add* is set for the fall and rising again of many
in Israel; and for a sign which shall be spoken against;

And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel,
of the tribe of Aser: she was of a great age, and had lived with
an husband seven years from her virginity;

Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought
low; and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways \add shall
be\add* made smooth;

\wj  For nothing is secret, that shall not be made manifest;
neither \+add any thing\+add* hid, that shall not be known and come
abroad.\wj*

¶ While he yet spake, there cometh one from the ruler of the
synagogue’s \add house\add*, saying to him, Thy daughter is dead;
trouble not the Master.

And he said unto them, \wj  Take nothing for \+add your\+add*
journey, neither staves, nor scrip, neither bread, neither money;
neither have two coats apiece.\wj*

¶ Now Herod the tetrarch heard of all that was done by him:
and he was perplexed, because that it was said of some, that John
was risen from the dead;

And, lo, a spirit taketh him, and he suddenly crieth out;
and it teareth him that he foameth again, and bruising him hardly
departeth from him.

\wj  For I tell you, that many prophets and kings have desired
to see those things which ye see, and have not seen \+add them\+add*;
and to hear those things which ye hear, and have not heard \+add them.\+add*\wj*

¶ And he said also to the people, \wj  When ye see a cloud
rise out of the west, straightway ye say, There cometh a shower;
and so it is.\wj*

\wj  It is neither fit for the land, nor yet for the dunghill;
\+add but\+add* men cast it out. He that hath ears to hear, let him
hear.\wj*

\wj  And beside all this, between us and you there is a great
gulf fixed: so that they which would pass from hence to you cannot;
neither can they pass to us, that \+add would come\+add* from thence.\wj*

Saying, \wj  Go ye into the village over against \+add you\+add*;
in the which at your entering ye shall find a colt tied, whereon
yet never man sat: loose him, and bring \+add him hither\+add*.\wj*

\wj  And shall lay thee even with the ground, and thy children
within thee; and they shall not leave in thee one stone upon another;
because thou knewest not the time of thy visitation.\wj*

\wj  Then let them which are in Judæa flee to the mountains;
and let them which are in the midst of it depart out; and let not
them that are in the countries enter thereinto.\wj*

\wj ¶ And there shall be signs in the sun, and in the moon,
and in the stars; and upon the earth distress of nations, with perplexity;
the sea and the waves roaring;\wj*

And he said unto them, \wj  Behold, when ye are entered into
the city, there shall a man meet you, bearing a pitcher of water;
follow him into the house where he entereth in.\wj*

Then said he unto them, \wj  But now, he that hath a purse,
let him take \+add it\+add*, and likewise \+add his\+add* scrip:
and he that hath no sword, let him sell his garment, and buy one.\wj*
